# Settings

You can use settings functions to configure custom transcoding templates, watermark templates, and MPS queues.

## Custom transcoding template

1.  Log on to the [Media Processing console](https://mts.console.aliyun.com/?spm=5176.2020520001.0.0.6RsosT#/mts/oss).
2.  Log on to the [Media Processing console](https://partners-intl.aliyun.com/login-required#/mts).
3.  Click **Settings**.
4.  Select the region.
5.  Click **Transcoding Templates**, and click **Create** to create a custom transcoding template.

    ![](images/10055_en-US.png)

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954010056_en-US.png)

6.  Select the **Output Format**.

    Set the **Template Name** and **File Format**.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954410057_en-US.png)

    **Note:** For more information about the supported transcoding output formats, see [Supported formats](/intl.en-US/API Reference/Appendix/Supported formats.md).

7.  Set the **Video Parameters**.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954410058_en-US.png)

    **Note:** If you select **Disable Video**, the output file does not include video information. This option is applicable when audio information is extracted from a video file. For more information about the video transcoding parameters, see [Video parameters](/intl.en-US/API Reference/Appendix/Parameter details.md).

8.  Set the **Audio Parameters**.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954410059_en-US.png)

    **Note:** If you select **Disable Video**, the output file does not include video information. This option is applicable when audio information is extracted from a video file. For more information about the video transcoding parameters, see [Audio parameters](/intl.en-US/API Reference/Appendix/Parameter details.md).

9.  Set the **Conditional**.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954510060_en-US.png)

10. Set the Container Parameters.

    The Container Parameters are set only when the output format is M3U8. You can set the slice duration of each TS file.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954510061_en-US.png)

11. Click **OK**. The template is created.

    You can view, edit, and delete transcoding parameter configurations in the transcoding template list.

    ![](images/10062_en-US.png)

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954110063_en-US.png)


## Watermark transcoding template

1.  Click **Watermark Templates** \> **Create** to create a watermark template.

    A maximum of 20 static images in PNG format can be added to an output video.

    ![](images/10064_en-US.png)

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954110065_en-US.png)

2.  Set the watermark template parameters.

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954510066_en-US.png)

    **Note:** For more information about the watermark template parameters, see [Watermark template parameters](/intl.en-US/API Reference/Appendix/Parameter details.md).

3.  Click **OK**, and the watermark template is created.

    You can view, edit, and delete parameter configurations in a watermark template in the watermark template list.

    ![](images/10067_en-US.png)

    ![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954110068_en-US.png)


## MPS queue

When a workflow is executed, it separates transcoding and other operation nodes into independent transcoding tasks, and puts them in MPS Queues. An MPS queue schedules and executes tasks. If an MPS queue is in the **Pause status**, tasks generated by all workflows using this MPS queue wait in the MPS Queues.

![](images/10069_en-US.png)

![](https://static-aliyun-doc.oss-accelerate.aliyuncs.com/assets/img/11363/154382954110070_en-US.png)

